#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:111
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config COMMAND [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"View and modify the shared FSearch GUI and CLI configuration.\n"
"\n"
"Configuration commands:\n"
"  path                         Print the configuration file path\n"
"  show [SECTION] [--json]      Show settings\n"
"  get KEY [--json]             Print one scalar setting\n"
"  set KEY VALUE                Set one scalar setting\n"
"  unset KEY                    Restore one scalar setting default\n"
"  reset [KEY|SECTION] --yes [--rescan]\n"
"                               Restore defaults\n"
"  doctor                       Check configuration and index consistency\n"
"  roots list|add|set|remove    Manage indexed roots\n"
"  excludes list|add|remove|hidden\n"
"                               Manage index exclusions\n"
"  filters list|add|set|remove|reset\n"
"                               Manage saved search filters\n"
"\n"
"Scalar values use true/false, decimal integers, or strings.\n"
"Run 'fsearch config show' to list every scalar key and current value.\n"
"Scalar sections: search, application, window, ui, columns, sort, dialogs.\n"
"Use 'fsearch config roots|excludes|filters --help' for family options.\n"
"Close the FSearch GUI before changing shared settings.\n"
"Index changes become searchable on the next CLI search, or immediately with "
"--rescan.\n"
"Use --json with show, get, and collection list commands.\n"
"\n"
"Examples:\n"
"  fsearch config show search --json\n"
"  fsearch config get search.match-case\n"
"  fsearch config set search.match-case true\n"
"  fsearch config roots add ~/Code --monitor --one-file-system --rescan\n"
"  fsearch config excludes add '*.tmp' --type wildcard --scope basename --"
"target files\n"
"  fsearch config filters add Documents --query 'ext:pdf' --macro docs\n"
"  fsearch config reset search --yes\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config COMMAND [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Afficher et modifier la configuration partagée par l’interface graphique et "
"la CLI de FSearch.\n"
"\n"
"Commandes de configuration :\n"
"  path                         Afficher le chemin du fichier de "
"configuration\n"
"  show [SECTION] [--json]      Afficher les paramètres\n"
"  get KEY [--json]             Afficher un paramètre scalaire\n"
"  set KEY VALUE                Définir un paramètre scalaire\n"
"  unset KEY                    Rétablir la valeur par défaut d’un paramètre "
"scalaire\n"
"  reset [KEY|SECTION] --yes [--rescan]\n"
"                               Rétablir les valeurs par défaut\n"
"  doctor                       Vérifier la cohérence de la configuration et "
"de l’index\n"
"  roots list|add|set|remove    Gérer les racines indexées\n"
"  excludes list|add|remove|hidden\n"
"                               Gérer les exclusions de l’index\n"
"  filters list|add|set|remove|reset\n"
"                               Gérer les filtres de recherche enregistrés\n"
"\n"
"Les valeurs scalaires utilisent true/false, des entiers décimaux ou des "
"chaînes.\n"
"Exécutez 'fsearch config show' pour afficher chaque clé scalaire et sa "
"valeur actuelle.\n"
"Sections scalaires : search, application, window, ui, columns, sort, "
"dialogs.\n"
"Utilisez 'fsearch config roots|excludes|filters --help' pour les options de "
"chaque famille.\n"
"Fermez l’interface graphique de FSearch avant de modifier les paramètres "
"partagés.\n"
"Les modifications de l’index seront prises en compte lors de la prochaine "
"recherche par la CLI, ou immédiatement avec --rescan.\n"
"Utilisez --json avec les commandes show, get et les commandes list des "
"collections.\n"
"\n"
"Exemples :\n"
"  fsearch config show search --json\n"
"  fsearch config get search.match-case\n"
"  fsearch config set search.match-case true\n"
"  fsearch config roots add ~/Code --monitor --one-file-system --rescan\n"
"  fsearch config excludes add '*.tmp' --type wildcard --scope basename --"
"target files\n"
"  fsearch config filters add Documents --query 'ext:pdf' --macro docs\n"
"  fsearch config reset search --yes\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:152
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config show [SECTION] [--json]\n"
"Show all scalar settings or one dotted section.\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config show [SECTION] [--json]\n"
"Afficher tous les paramètres scalaires ou une section en notation pointée.\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:154
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config get KEY [--json]\n"
"Print one typed scalar value. Discover keys with 'fsearch config show'.\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config get KEY [--json]\n"
"Afficher une valeur scalaire typée. Découvrez les clés avec 'fsearch config "
"show'.\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:157
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config set KEY VALUE\n"
"Set a boolean, integer, string, or enumerated scalar value.\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config set KEY VALUE\n"
"Définir une valeur scalaire booléenne, entière, textuelle ou énumérée.\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:159
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config unset KEY\n"
"Restore one scalar setting to its built-in default.\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config unset KEY\n"
"Rétablir la valeur par défaut intégrée d’un paramètre scalaire.\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:161
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config reset [KEY|SECTION] --yes [--rescan]\n"
"Reset is destructive and requires --yes. --rescan applies to roots, "
"database, excludes, or all.\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config reset [KEY|SECTION] --yes [--rescan]\n"
"La réinitialisation est destructive et nécessite --yes. --rescan s’applique "
"aux racines, à la base de données, aux exclusions ou à l’ensemble.\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:164
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config doctor\n"
"Check configuration readability and whether the saved index uses the same "
"roots and exclusions.\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config doctor\n"
"Vérifier la lisibilité de la configuration et si l’index enregistré utilise "
"les mêmes racines et exclusions.\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:170
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config roots COMMAND [PATH] [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Commands:\n"
"  list [--json]                List indexed roots\n"
"  add PATH [OPTIONS]           Add a root directory\n"
"  set PATH [OPTIONS]           Change an existing root\n"
"  remove PATH [--rescan]       Remove an existing root\n"
"\n"
"Options for add and set:\n"
"  --active, --inactive\n"
"  --monitor, --no-monitor\n"
"  --one-file-system, --no-one-file-system\n"
"  --scan-after-launch, --no-scan-after-launch\n"
"  --rescan-every SECONDS        Set periodic rescan interval; 0 disables it\n"
"  --rescan                      Rebuild the index immediately after saving\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config roots COMMAND [PATH] [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Commandes :\n"
"  list [--json]                Afficher les racines indexées\n"
"  add PATH [OPTIONS]           Ajouter un répertoire racine\n"
"  set PATH [OPTIONS]           Modifier une racine existante\n"
"  remove PATH [--rescan]       Supprimer une racine existante\n"
"\n"
"Options pour add et set :\n"
"  --active, --inactive\n"
"  --monitor, --no-monitor\n"
"  --one-file-system, --no-one-file-system\n"
"  --scan-after-launch, --no-scan-after-launch\n"
"  --rescan-every SECONDS        Définir l’intervalle d’analyse périodique ; "
"0 la désactive\n"
"  --rescan                      Reconstruire l’index immédiatement après "
"l’enregistrement\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:187
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config excludes COMMAND [PATTERN|VALUE] [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Commands:\n"
"  list [--json]                 List exclusions\n"
"  add PATTERN [OPTIONS]         Add an exclusion\n"
"  remove PATTERN [OPTIONS]      Remove a matching exclusion\n"
"  hidden [true|false] [--rescan]\n"
"                                View or change hidden-file exclusion\n"
"\n"
"Options for add and remove:\n"
"  --type fixed|wildcard|regex   Default: fixed\n"
"  --scope full-path|basename    Default: full-path\n"
"  --target both|files|folders   Default: both\n"
"  --active, --inactive          Add state or removal selector\n"
"  --rescan                      Rebuild the index immediately after saving\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config excludes COMMAND [PATTERN|VALUE] [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Commandes :\n"
"  list [--json]                 Afficher les exclusions\n"
"  add PATTERN [OPTIONS]         Ajouter une exclusion\n"
"  remove PATTERN [OPTIONS]      Supprimer une exclusion correspondante\n"
"  hidden [true|false] [--rescan]\n"
"                                Afficher ou modifier l’exclusion des "
"fichiers cachés\n"
"\n"
"Options pour add et remove :\n"
"  --type fixed|wildcard|regex   Valeur par défaut : fixed\n"
"  --scope full-path|basename    Valeur par défaut : full-path\n"
"  --target both|files|folders   Valeur par défaut : both\n"
"  --active, --inactive          État d’ajout ou sélecteur de suppression\n"
"  --rescan                      Reconstruire l’index immédiatement après "
"l’enregistrement\n"

#: src/fsearch_cli_config.c:204
msgid ""
"Usage: fsearch config filters COMMAND [NAME] [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Commands:\n"
"  list [--json]                 List saved filters\n"
"  add NAME [OPTIONS]            Add a named filter\n"
"  set NAME [OPTIONS]            Change a named filter\n"
"  remove NAME                   Remove a named filter\n"
"  reset                         Restore built-in filters\n"
"\n"
"Options for add and set:\n"
"  --query QUERY                 Saved FSearch query\n"
"  --macro MACRO                 Query macro name\n"
"  --case, --no-case             Match case\n"
"  --path, --no-path             Search full paths\n"
"  --regex, --no-regex           Treat query as a regular expression\n"
msgstr ""
"Utilisation : fsearch config filters COMMAND [NAME] [OPTIONS]\n"
"\n"
"Commandes :\n"
"  list [--json]                 Afficher les filtres enregistrés\n"
"  add NAME [OPTIONS]            Ajouter un filtre nommé\n"
"  set NAME [OPTIONS]            Modifier un filtre nommé\n"
"  remove NAME                   Supprimer un filtre nommé\n"
"  reset                         Rétablir les filtres intégrés\n"
"\n"
"Options pour add et set :\n"
"  --query QUERY                 Requête FSearch enregistrée\n"
"  --macro MACRO                 Nom de la macro de requête\n"
"  --case, --no-case             Respecter la casse\n"
"  --path, --no-path             Rechercher dans les chemins complets\n"
"  --regex, --no-regex           Traiter la requête comme une expression "
"régulière\n"

